<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7945c230-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s719n"><num value="719n">§ 719n.</num><heading> Separability</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If any provision of this chapter, or the application thereof, is held invalid, the remainder of this chapter shall not be affected thereby.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7945c231-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/94/586/s16">Pub. L. 94–586, § 16</ref>, <date date="1976-10-22">Oct. 22, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/2915">90 Stat. 2915</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
